  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "FSbULqv4Koe95+Bm/sq3zMZj7+Y=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Key derivation (one-time)\n\n```\npersonal_sign(\"Sign to derive Swarm key...\")\n  -> keccak256(signature)\n  -> 32-byte private key\n  -> cached in IndexedDB  (no repeated signing)\n```\n\nBecause `personal_sign` is deterministic per message, **same wallet = same key = same access**. Recovery on a new device only needs the wallet.\n\n## Operation batch encryption\n\nEvery batch uploaded to `/bytes` is AES-256-GCM encrypted before upload and decrypted after download. Payload format:\n\n```\n[SWE prefix (3B)] [IV (12B)] [ciphertext]\n```\n\nThe SWE prefix is a magic-byte marker that lets the client reject any payload it accidentally reads that was not produced by this pipeline.\n\n## Feed authentication\n\nFeeds are signed with the same wallet-derived Swarm private key \u2014 only the owner can write, but anyone with the owner's public key (i.e. anyone who knows the Ethereum address) can read.\n\n## Where it lives\n\n- `adapter/src/swarm-crypto.ts` \u2014 AES-256-GCM encrypt/decrypt.\n- `adapter/src/wallet-signer.ts` \u2014 wallet signature to key derivation.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:48.000Z"
    }
  },
